<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="96" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="96">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="96">Mentum without foveae; foretibia with apicolateral notch; body subdepressed, flavotestaceous, shiny; head with single pair of supraorbital setae; basal protarsomere of male dilated, medially dentiform; head (3), pronotum (5), and elytron (8) with prominent longitudinal carinae; ABL = 1.7-2.6 mm.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
